column6: Hello! I'm VirtualCarolyn. Take a minute to introduce yourselves.
I am gaurav
Nice to meet you, Gaurav.
While I won't answer your questions directly, I can help guide your group discussion.
animal
Once you get an idea of what's going on, replace these prompts with something domain appropriate!
cow
We can work on your basic zoology. Are you ready?
yes
Let's get started.
There are three kinds of animals - birds, fish, and mammals.
Can you tell me something about some kind of animal?
cow
...that's a mammal!
Let's try something harder - what kind of animal gives birth to live young?
mammal
Sounds good...
You're ready to be a zoologist!
Now I'll start an interactive dialogue.
Even if you disable tutorial triggers, you can still have dialogues in your macro-script.
Note that other agent behaviors (like accountable-talk style listening) will be suppressed while the dialogue is underway.
(You can trigger the same tutorial dynamically by talking about animals - see dialouges/dialogues-example.xml and dictionaries/animals.txt for details)
Okay, that's all I've got planned. I'll stick around, but it's up to you to lead the discussion.
I can't do this on my own :-)
